content:
You are here: SALESFORCE HELP

Manage Call Center Users

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Essentials to Unlimited Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED:
Manage Call Centers

A user must be assigned to a call center by an administrator to use a softphone.

Call center users have personal softphone settings for:

* Automatic login into softphone
* Display of incoming call record

Change default settings using Lightning Platform API.

Add a User to a Call Center: Enable users to make or receive phone calls.
Remove a User from a Call Center: Delete the user from the call center.

SEE ALSO:
Open CTI Developer Guide, Set Up a Call Center, Create a Call Center, Manage Call Centers
title: Managing Call Center Users in Salesforce
